items.title: Cosmic 9-9-9 alignment: Wealth creation or risk of sharp reversal?
items.description: As markets open on September 9, 2025, they do so in the wake of a potent lunar event: the total lunar eclipse (Chandra Grahan) that occurs on September 7–8, widely visible across India.

items.title: Modi-Xi handshake, tax cuts boost case for lagging Indian stocks
items.description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s symbolic handshake with President Xi Jinping in China, combined with fresh tax cuts at home, is fueling optimism that Indian equities will finally narrow the gap with their emerging-market peers.

items.title: FII activity, India-US trade deal among 7 factors that may impact D-Street action this week
items.description: Indian equity benchmarks wrapped up the week on a solid note, buoyed by strong domestic macroeconomic data and ongoing policy reforms. The Nifty gained 1.29% to settle at 24,741, while the Sensex climbed 1.13% to close at 80,710.
